04:00.600 --> 04:04.600
I'm sorry, I'm so sorry.

04:05.600 --> 04:07.900
Why can't you mother
clean out the coffeemaker?

04:07.900 --> 04:11.200
No. Dad... I meant...

04:12.200 --> 04:15.900
No. Sweetie, don't do that, all right?
You been crying for weeks.

04:15.900 --> 04:16.899
Come on.

04:17.700 --> 04:19.200
It's OK.

04:19.200 --> 04:23.200
OK, it's not OK, but... I just
don't know how this happened.

04:23.400 --> 04:26.400
I mean how'd it happen, Amy?
How is this possible?

04:27.300 --> 04:29.100
Sex?

04:31.300 --> 04:34.800
I guess I should've talked to
you more about personal stuff.

04:35.000 --> 04:36.500
Guys.

04:36.900 --> 04:39.000
Where babies come from.

04:39.400 --> 04:43.100
But... you really think you wanna go
away and live with your grandmother?

04:43.100 --> 04:45.000
I mean, you think
that's the best thing?

04:45.600 --> 04:46.500
Yeah.

04:46.500 --> 04:49.200
Was that your idea
or your mom's idea?

04:49.300 --> 04:51.400
I don't wanna stay here, Dad.

04:52.100 --> 04:54.500
I don't wanna face everybody.

04:54.600 --> 04:56.000
What about Ben?

04:56.100 --> 04:58.600
I still wanna marry him, but...

04:58.600 --> 05:00.900
but Mom still thinks it's a bad idea.

05:01.900 --> 05:03.400
What do you think?

05:03.400 --> 05:05.500
Do you have any new
thoughts on that?

05:05.500 --> 05:08.000
Maybe later... when you're 30.

05:08.000 --> 05:09.200
Yeah.

05:09.200 --> 05:12.700
When the baby's my age - 15.

05:12.700 --> 05:15.200
Honey, everything's gonna be OK.

05:15.200 --> 05:17.600
These things happen.

05:17.600 --> 05:21.400
Mainly when guys talk young girls
into doing things they shouldn't.

05:21.400 --> 05:24.100
It's not all his fault.
I just let it happen.

05:24.100 --> 05:26.600
No, it's his fault.
He knew what he was doing.

05:26.700 --> 05:29.200
And this Ricky guy -
he knows about this?

05:29.500 --> 05:30.600
Yeah, he knows.

05:30.600 --> 05:32.200
But you haven't talked
to him face to face.

05:32.200 --> 05:33.200
No.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.300
I don't want anything
to do with that guy.

05:35.500 --> 05:37.300
Little late for that.

05:38.500 --> 05:41.800
After yo u have the, um... 

05:41.800 --> 05:45.100
child, then what?

05:46.800 --> 05:49.000
I don't know.

05:49.000 --> 05:52.300
I can't think about that
right now, Daddy.

05:55.000 --> 05:58.100
You haven't called me that
in so long, baby.

05:59.200 --> 06:00.700
Aw, Amy...

06:01.000 --> 06:03.200
Oh.

06:03.300 --> 06:07.000
Maybe it really is time
for me to come home.

06:12.400 --> 06:14.400
So, what are you gonna do?

06:14.400 --> 06:15.800
I'm not gonna do anything.

06:15.800 --> 06:17.400
Have you talked to her?

06:17.400 --> 06:19.400
No, I haven't talked to her.

06:19.400 --> 06:20.500
Well, talk to her.

06:20.500 --> 06:22.900
I don't wanna talk to her.
I don't want anything to do with her.

06:22.900 --> 06:25.600
You've already had something
to do with her, son.

06:25.700 --> 06:27.200
You are not my dad.

06:27.200 --> 06:31.100
You're right, I'm not, but I've tried
to be a good father to you,

06:31.100 --> 06:33.600
and now you're gonna be a father, so...

06:33.600 --> 06:35.600
what kind of father
are you gonna be?

06:35.600 --> 06:37.600
It's time to have a conversation.

06:37.600 --> 06:41.600
Go talk to her, today, this
morning before you go to school.

06:42.000 --> 06:44.100
I'm already late,
and don't you think

06:44.100 --> 06:46.100
if she wanted to talk to me,
she'd come talk to me?

06:46.100 --> 06:47.900
She knows where to find me.

06:47.900 --> 06:49.100
We have band together.

06:49.100 --> 06:51.200
So is she gonna stay in school?

06:51.200 --> 06:52.700
How would I know?

06:52.700 --> 06:54.700
Wait, how could she stay in school?

06:54.700 --> 06:56.200
She does have that option.

06:56.200 --> 06:59.800
She's not gonna come to school
when she's having a baby.

06:59.800 --> 07:01.800
Can't you do something about that?

07:01.800 --> 07:03.800
What would you want me to do?

07:03.800 --> 07:05.300
Aren't you a social worker?

07:05.300 --> 07:06.100
Yes.

07:06.100 --> 07:09.800
And I encourage teenage mothers
to stay in school.

07:10.000 --> 07:11.500
Are you kidding me?

07:11.500 --> 07:15.200
No, I am not
kidding you, Ricky.

07:15.200 --> 07:18.700
I encourage you
to take responsibility

07:18.700 --> 07:21.100
for whatever happens
to this baby.

07:21.100 --> 07:25.200
Not exactly the responsible type
and neither is she, thus the baby.

07:31.900 --> 07:33.400
Any word yet?

07:33.400 --> 07:36.200
We're running out of time.
We gotta get you to school.

07:36.200 --> 07:37.500
I haven't heard anything yet.

07:37.500 --> 07:39.500
All I know she wants to leave town.

07:39.500 --> 07:41.300
It's not that far away
to grandmother house.

07:41.300 --> 07:43.700
We can drive up
on the weekends and see Ames.

07:44.000 --> 07:45.700
She doesn't want us to see her.

07:45.700 --> 07:48.000
Or at least she doesn't
want me to see her.

07:48.000 --> 07:49.700
Is that crazy, or what?

07:49.700 --> 07:51.300
She's scared, Ben.

07:51.300 --> 07:53.900
I mean she's scared and she's
angry and she's overwhelmed.

07:53.900 --> 07:59.100
Do her and yourself a favor and go
along with the plan, whatever it is.

07:59.100 --> 08:01.200
Of course, whatever it is is
probably gonna change 

08:01.200 --> 08:02.800
over and over and over again.

08:02.800 --> 08:04.700
It's just not easy, that's all.

08:04.700 --> 08:07.600
What in life is easy?
Not much, that's what.

08:08.400 --> 08:10.200
Certainly not
the sausage business.

08:10.300 --> 08:12.900
Come on,
we better get going.

08:13.000 --> 08:13.900
Dad...

08:14.000 --> 08:16.700
I know, you wanna stay home.

08:16.900 --> 08:19.600
I'm pretty sure your mother
would want you to go to school.

08:19.600 --> 08:20.700
I don't think she would.

08:20.700 --> 08:23.400
All right, stay home,
as long as it's for one day.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.200
You don't wanna stay home
and hang out with me?

08:25.200 --> 08:26.900
No. Can't do, I'd rather stay busy.

08:26.900 --> 08:28.600
And besides...

08:28.700 --> 08:30.800
I'm pretty sure you
don't have any intention 

08:30.800 --> 08:32.900
of hanging around
the house all day.

08:33.000 --> 08:34.299
Am I wrong?

08:34.400 --> 08:35.100
No.

08:39.600 --> 08:42.600
Call her, text her, do something.

08:42.600 --> 08:44.700
Let me know what happens.

09:02.500 --> 09:03.500
Hello.

09:03.500 --> 09:05.100
I love you.

09:05.100 --> 09:06.200
Me too.

09:06.200 --> 09:07.800
Is he still there?

09:07.800 --> 09:09.100
No, he's gone.

09:09.100 --> 09:10.200
Then what's the decision?

09:10.200 --> 09:11.400
Decision?

09:11.400 --> 09:12.200
Are you goin'?

09:12.200 --> 09:13.600
Yeah.

09:13.800 --> 09:15.900
I'm going to my grandmother's.

09:16.100 --> 09:18.000
I thought maybe your dad
would say no.

09:18.000 --> 09:21.400
I think that's kinda up to me
to decide, don't you?

09:21.400 --> 09:25.100
Ben, you can't decide for me.
I have to go. I can't stay.

09:25.100 --> 09:27.000
Stay with me, at my house.

09:27.000 --> 09:28.700
I mean just say you're going to
your grandmother's,

09:28.700 --> 09:30.200
and live with me and my dad.

09:30.200 --> 09:33.000
I can't do that. I don't
want you to see me, either.

09:33.000 --> 09:35.400
I have to see you.
I'll die if I don't see you.

09:35.400 --> 09:38.700
OK, please don't say that.
We both know you're not gonna die.

09:38.700 --> 09:41.600
It makes me feel like
you're threatening to kill yourself.

09:41.600 --> 09:47.300
OK, one - "I'll feel really bad if I don't
see you" doesn't express my true feelings,

09:47.300 --> 09:49.900
and two - I think you're aware
that when you lose a parent,

09:49.900 --> 09:51.600
it makes you value your own life,

09:51.600 --> 09:55.200
so I have no intention of offing myself.

09:55.300 --> 09:58.100
I totally just forgot about your mom.

09:58.300 --> 10:00.300
Say something, please?

10:00.300 --> 10:03.500
You really think going to your
grandmother's is the only solution?

10:03.500 --> 10:05.100
No, I don't think
there is any solution,

10:05.100 --> 10:07.800
but I do think
it'll make things easier.

10:07.800 --> 10:09.300
Ben, this isn't easy.

10:09.300 --> 10:12.300
What is?
Not much, that's what.

10:12.300 --> 10:13.100
What?

10:13.100 --> 10:14.000
Nothing.

10:14.000 --> 10:17.300
Why is it going to be easier for people
to see you after you've had the baby?

10:17.300 --> 10:19.200
Either way, they know.

10:19.200 --> 10:21.300
Just don't care if they know.
Don't care.

10:21.300 --> 10:25.100
You can decide that, you know,
to not care what people think.

10:25.100 --> 10:26.600
Who doesn't care
what people think?

10:26.600 --> 10:28.100
Me. I don't care.

10:28.100 --> 10:31.000
Come on, Amy. At least consider
going back to school.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.100
I'll be right there with you,
holding your hand.

10:33.100 --> 10:34.900
I already told you I can't.

10:34.900 --> 10:37.300
They're a bunch
of high school students.

10:37.300 --> 10:40.100
Ben, I'm going to my grandmother's.

10:40.800 --> 10:43.700
You can come over tonight
and say goodbye if you want.

10:43.700 --> 10:45.400
I'll probably leave
in the morning.

10:45.400 --> 10:46.400
No.

10:46.400 --> 10:50.300
Thanks for asking, but, no,
I don't wanna say goodbye,

10:50.300 --> 10:54.100
because I don't want you
to leave.

11:07.300 --> 11:08.600
Who is it?

11:08.600 --> 11:10.100
It's me.

11:13.700 --> 11:14.800
What are you doing here?

11:14.800 --> 11:16.200
Come on,
let's stay home today.

11:16.200 --> 11:17.100
I can't.

11:17.100 --> 11:18.000
Why?

11:18.000 --> 11:19.300
'Cause I don't want to.

11:19.500 --> 11:22.300
All right. Can I stay here?

11:22.500 --> 11:24.300
I'm not in the mood
to go to school today.

11:24.300 --> 11:25.400
You can't stay here.

11:25.400 --> 11:26.400
Is your mom home?

11:26.400 --> 11:27.500
You know she's not.

11:27.500 --> 11:30.200
Come on, Adrian. I can't
go to school today.

11:30.200 --> 11:30.600
I can't.

11:30.600 --> 11:32.500
Sedlack will kill you
if you don't make practice.

11:32.500 --> 11:35.100
I'm already missing practice,
and I don't care about band.

11:35.100 --> 11:37.000
Can I come in?

11:44.300 --> 11:46.000
I need you.

11:46.100 --> 11:47.700
Oh, come on.

11:48.100 --> 11:50.100
My life is falling apart.
I need you.

11:50.100 --> 11:51.900
Really. Just take a day off.

11:51.900 --> 11:54.300
Call in sick, stay in bed.

11:56.100 --> 11:57.900
Mnh-mnh. I have to turn in
my English Lit paper.

11:57.900 --> 11:58.900
Turn it in tomorrow.

11:58.900 --> 12:01.300
No. I worked really hard on it.

12:01.300 --> 12:02.500
I'm not gonna
get points taken off

12:02.500 --> 12:04.900
just 'cause I didn't
turn it in on time.

12:06.300 --> 12:10.300
OK, I'll come back at lunch,
after English Lit.

12:15.500 --> 12:17.900
You can stay,
but I have to go.

12:28.400 --> 12:30.000
What are you doing home?

12:30.800 --> 12:33.200
Come on, you didn't think
I was actually going to school.

12:33.200 --> 12:36.200
We're parent-free.

12:36.300 --> 12:38.500
So, how'd it go with Dad?

12:40.100 --> 12:43.700
I don't know. He cried,
and I cried...

12:43.700 --> 12:44.700
Yeah, and?

12:44.700 --> 12:47.200
And he wants to come home.

12:47.200 --> 12:48.700
Thank you. Finally.

12:48.700 --> 12:51.500
Just because he says that
does not mean she'll let him.

12:51.500 --> 12:55.300
And aren't you concerned you're gonna
get in trouble for ditching school?

12:56.800 --> 12:59.000
Yeah.

12:59.000 --> 13:00.700
Guess I kinda
lowered that bar.

13:00.700 --> 13:03.700
Thank you for that, too.

13:04.900 --> 13:08.400
Don't you think you're taking this
whole thing a little too seriously?

13:08.400 --> 13:11.100
It's not like you're dying.
You're just having a baby.

13:11.100 --> 13:14.600
Just? Just having a baby?

13:14.600 --> 13:15.800
Ashley, I'm 15.

13:15.800 --> 13:17.300
I don't wanna have a baby.

13:17.300 --> 13:18.900
I just wanna be normal
like everyone else.

13:18.900 --> 13:20.900
I wanna go to a normal school
and be in the band

13:20.900 --> 13:23.900
and go to high school dances
and fall in love and get married

13:23.900 --> 13:25.800
and then maybe have a baby.

13:25.800 --> 13:27.800
Then why did you have sex?

13:27.800 --> 13:28.500
I don't know.

13:28.500 --> 13:29.900
I didn't... think about it.

13:29.900 --> 13:32.600
I didn't have a good reason.
I just did it.

13:32.800 --> 13:35.600
Ashley, promise me that you won't
have sex until marriage.

13:35.600 --> 13:37.900
Please. Not one of your fake
promises to Mom and Dad.

13:37.900 --> 13:40.000
A real promise. 

13:40.000 --> 13:41.600
I don't want you to make
the same mistake I did.

13:41.600 --> 13:43.200
Are you kidding?

13:43.200 --> 13:45.300
I have condoms.
I'm not an idiot.

13:45.300 --> 13:46.800
You have condoms at 13?

13:46.800 --> 13:48.100
Where did you get condoms?

13:48.100 --> 13:49.200
The grocery store.

13:49.200 --> 13:51.400
You are not using condoms.

13:51.400 --> 13:53.900
Now there's some really bad advice.

13:53.900 --> 13:56.500
OK, you know what I mean, Ashley.

13:56.500 --> 13:58.400
You don't need condoms.
Just say no.

13:58.400 --> 14:00.300
That doesn't work, obviously.

14:00.300 --> 14:02.200
I didn't say no.
I didn't say anything.

14:02.200 --> 14:03.900
I just let this happen.

14:03.900 --> 14:06.600
I cannot believe
I let this happen to me.

14:06.900 --> 14:08.900
Ashley, just listen to me.

14:08.900 --> 14:10.700
You do not wanna have a baby.

14:10.700 --> 14:13.100
Not at 13. That's why
I have the condoms.

14:13.100 --> 14:14.900
When did you even
get condoms?

14:14.900 --> 14:17.600
I dunno. Right after
I found out you were pregnant.

14:17.600 --> 14:19.800
It's not like they're illegal.
Anyone can buy 'em.

14:20.000 --> 14:23.100
Why are you in such a bad mood
this morning?

14:23.100 --> 14:24.600
I thought it was
because Dad was coming over,

14:24.600 --> 14:26.100
but that's obviously not it.

14:26.100 --> 14:27.600
I'm not in a bad mood.

14:27.600 --> 14:30.200
Yeah, you're right.
You're in an angry mood.

14:31.300 --> 14:33.700
What, are you angry at that guy Ricky?

14:33.700 --> 14:35.900
No. I'm just angry
with myself.

14:35.900 --> 14:37.300
No, that's not it.

14:37.300 --> 14:39.900
What, is it Ben?

14:39.900 --> 14:41.900
God, how can you be angry
with a guy who loves you

14:41.900 --> 14:44.600
despite the fact that
you're pregnant by another guy?

14:44.600 --> 14:45.700
I just can, OK?

14:45.700 --> 14:49.200
Well, it's a step up
from feeling sorry for yourself.

14:54.500 --> 14:56.000
Change your mind?

14:57.500 --> 14:59.200
Who are you?

