for a while.

33:38.248 --> 33:40.215
For a while. Get it?

33:40.216 --> 33:42.341
She's not leaving forever.

33:42.341 --> 33:44.218
She's choosing to go.

33:45.273 --> 33:48.509
Mom, she didn't have a choice,
but Amy is...

33:48.509 --> 33:51.096
You can't have your way
on this one, Benjamin.

33:51.493 --> 33:54.104
Jue I couldn't
have my way on that one.

33:54.631 --> 33:56.087
Live with it.

34:25.569 --> 34:27.138
I'm really happy
you stopped by.

34:27.138 --> 34:29.068
And surprised.

34:29.068 --> 34:30.295
Yes, we're very happy.

34:30.295 --> 34:33.601
We're very happy.
We've heard so much about you.

34:33.601 --> 34:37.858
From me. That's why
we are surprised.

34:37.858 --> 34:38.980
Yeah.

34:39.233 --> 34:45.246
I remember the other time
I was surprised to see you.

34:45.246 --> 34:48.121
Why don't we just
let that go, Tom? Let it go.

34:48.757 --> 34:50.940
Really. We're really happy
you stopped by.

34:50.940 --> 34:52.322
I didn't have your number.

34:52.322 --> 34:55.503
I don't usually just
stop by anywhere.

34:55.503 --> 34:57.548
I don't even know why
I did this.

34:57.548 --> 34:59.915
Maybe it's because I asked
if you wanted to be friends.

35:00.102 --> 35:01.931
I'd really like to be friends.

35:01.932 --> 35:03.194
Really?

35:03.194 --> 35:05.678
Yeah, Grace is friends
with lots of people, Tom.

35:05.855 --> 35:07.755
Lots of people.
She's very friendly.

35:08.324 --> 35:10.863
Um, are you hungry?

35:10.864 --> 35:11.936
Have you had dinner?

35:11.936 --> 35:14.519
I'm not hungry. I don't
usually eat this early.

35:14.519 --> 35:16.767
We don't either, but my wife
had a function at church,

35:16.768 --> 35:17.847
lots of leftovers,

35:17.847 --> 35:20.765
so I can fix you a plate.
I'll get you something.

35:20.765 --> 35:22.549
No, I'm really
not hungry.

35:22.549 --> 35:24.559
Is it me?

35:24.559 --> 35:27.683
Sometimes
I make people nervous.

35:27.684 --> 35:29.059
Oh, no.I like you.

35:29.059 --> 35:30.487
You seem to be pretty honest.

35:30.487 --> 35:32.562
Yeah, I am.

35:32.562 --> 35:35.187
-Well, not that many people are honest.
-Yeah.

35:35.187 --> 35:37.157
-Yeah.
-True.

35:37.157 --> 35:42.236
I know. You thought Ricky
is here.

35:42.236 --> 35:43.860
Oh, no. I know where he is.

35:43.861 --> 35:46.282
Is he at Amy's?

35:46.282 --> 35:48.931
-And you would know that how?
-I was guessing.

35:48.931 --> 35:50.808
I told you at school
I thought maybe Ricky

35:50.808 --> 35:53.760
was capable of taking some
 responsibility for what happened.

35:54.234 --> 35:56.315
Not that I know him
better than you.

35:56.879 --> 35:58.798
I'm just an optimistic person.

35:58.798 --> 36:01.869
Just being optimistic,
hoping for the best.

36:01.869 --> 36:03.943
And in this situation,
what do you think is the best?

36:03.943 --> 36:07.299
Ahem. Why don't you let me
take this one, all right?

36:07.299 --> 36:12.411
Um, in this situation, I think the very
 best possible choice for Amy and Ricky

36:12.411 --> 36:15.869
would be to find a loving family
to adopt the baby.

36:15.869 --> 36:17.498
That way,
when the baby grows up,

36:17.498 --> 36:20.196
he or she can be thankful
to both of them

36:20.196 --> 36:23.130
for providing a loving family
that has two adults

36:23.130 --> 36:26.239
that can actually
take care of him or her.

36:26.239 --> 36:28.647
Yeah. That's good.

36:28.907 --> 36:31.599
Tell you what - Tom,
why don't we give the girls

36:31.599 --> 36:34.033
a little private time
to talk? What do you say?

36:36.555 --> 36:38.004
Good night.

36:39.309 --> 36:40.562
Really nice to meet you.

36:40.563 --> 36:41.570
You too.

36:51.539 --> 36:53.696
I don't wanna talk
about this anymore.

36:53.696 --> 36:55.980
I don't wanna talk
about Ricky or the baby.

36:55.980 --> 36:58.383
I thought I did,
but I don't.

36:58.383 --> 37:02.289
I don't know, I didn't want him
to be my only option tonight.

37:03.395 --> 37:04.477
I should go.

37:04.478 --> 37:05.634
No, please, stay.

37:05.634 --> 37:07.737
When you drop by, you're
supposed to stay a while.

37:07.737 --> 37:08.912
There are rules?

37:08.912 --> 37:11.216
No, but hang out.
We'll talk about something else.

37:11.217 --> 37:12.432
Anything else.

37:12.432 --> 37:14.073
Like?

37:14.073 --> 37:17.440
Like... I don't know.

37:17.935 --> 37:20.748
I don't have any girlfriends
that I do this with, either,

37:20.749 --> 37:21.764
so...

37:21.764 --> 37:23.679
I'm not really any better
at this than you.

37:30.693 --> 37:32.419
So what's new in your life?

37:33.888 --> 37:35.319
Oh, I got a new desk.

37:35.659 --> 37:37.486
A desk? That's great.

37:37.487 --> 37:39.109
 I'd love
to come see it sometime.

37:39.109 --> 37:40.405
OK.

37:40.901 --> 37:42.679
Where did you get it, online?

37:42.679 --> 37:44.406
I got a great desk online
one time.

37:44.407 --> 37:48.333
Uh, no.Actually, it was a gift
from my mother's boyfriend.

37:50.600 --> 37:51.738
Yeah.

37:56.605 --> 37:57.969
How'd you get home from school?

37:57.970 --> 37:59.125
Taxi.

37:59.125 --> 38:00.493
You don't have
that kind of cash.

38:00.565 --> 38:01.820
I took the bus.

38:01.820 --> 38:03.767
You don't even know
where the bus is.

38:03.767 --> 38:04.882
I walked.

38:04.882 --> 38:06.621
All the way home
from school?

38:09.046 --> 38:10.262
Do people at school know?

38:10.262 --> 38:11.305
Know what?

38:11.305 --> 38:12.792
About your sister?

38:12.792 --> 38:14.240
The whole world knows.

38:14.241 --> 38:15.049
How do they know?

38:15.049 --> 38:16.828
How does everyone know?

38:16.828 --> 38:19.731
Well, the people at school
have brothers and sisters

38:19.731 --> 38:21.327
who go to school with Amy.

38:24.061 --> 38:25.180
Welcome home, Dad.

38:25.181 --> 38:26.655
Hello, princess.

38:32.451 --> 38:35.325
I saw we had company,
so I came around the side.

38:35.853 --> 38:36.837
Whose car is that?

38:36.837 --> 38:37.892
Can he stay?

38:37.893 --> 38:39.951
Why don't you let
your father and I talk?

38:39.951 --> 38:43.267
Can't the three of us talk?
It is about the three of us,

38:43.267 --> 38:45.940
especially if Amy's
going off to Mimsy's.

38:45.941 --> 38:46.826
OK.

38:46.826 --> 38:49.294
Why don't we start with how
 you got home from school today?

38:49.733 --> 38:53.075
Right. I guess you have, um,

38:53.075 --> 38:56.768
more important things
to talk about than me.

39:01.495 --> 39:04.271
She hitched a ride with the bagboy
from the grocery store.

39:04.271 --> 39:05.349
The college kid?

39:05.529 --> 39:07.881
He saw her walking home
and picked her up.

39:08.498 --> 39:11.910
The cashier we like told me when I
 stopped in the market on the way home.

39:12.605 --> 39:14.837
